                     Lloyd C. Blankfein, chairman and chief executive officer of Goldman Sachs Group Inc., is sworn in before a Senate Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs subcommittee hearing on Wall Street and the financial crisis in Washington, D.C. Photographer: Andrew Harrer/Bloomberg  
                   
    

                 
           
                            
                     
                     Senator Carl Levin, a Democrat from Michigan, chairs a Senate Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs subcommittee hearing on Wall Street and the financial crisis in Washington, D.C., on April 27, 2010. Photographer: Andrew Harrer/Bloomberg  
                   
    

                 
           
                            
                     
                     Daniel Sparks, former partner and head of mortgages with Goldman Sachs Group Inc., left to right, Joshua Birnbaum, former managing director of structured products group trading with Goldman, Michael Swenson, managing director of structured products group trading with Goldman, and Fabrice Tourre, executive director of structured products group trading with Goldman, are sworn in during a Senate Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs subcommittee hearing on Wall Street and the financial crisis in Washington, D.C., on April 27, 2010. Photographer: Andrew Harrer/Bloomberg  
                   
    

                 
           
                            
                     
                     Protestors hold signs depicting Lloyd C. Blankfein, chairman and chief executive officer of Goldman Sachs Group Inc., and Fabrice Tourre, executive director of structured products group trading with Goldman, during a Senate Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs subcommittee hearing on Wall Street and the financial crisis in Washington, D.C., on April 27, 2010. Photographer: Andrew Harrer/Bloomberg  
                   
    

                 
           
                            
                     
                     Craig Broderick, chief risk officer of Goldman Sachs Group Inc., appears on a television screen as traders work on the floor of the New York Stock Exchange in New York on April 27, 2010. Photographer: Daniel Acker/Bloomberg  
                   
    

                 
           
                            
                     
                     Fabrice Tourre, executive director of structured products group trading with Goldman Sachs Group Inc., takes his seat before a Senate Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs subcommittee hearing on Wall Street and the financial crisis in Washington, D.C., on April 27, 2010. Photographer: Joshua Roberts/Bloomberg  
                   
    

                 
           
                            
                     
                     Fabrice Tourre, executive director of structured products group trading with Goldman Sachs Group Inc., rubs his eyes while testifying during a Senate Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs subcommittee hearing on Wall Street and the financial crisis in Washington, D.C., on April 27, 2010. Photographer: Andrew Harrer/Bloomberg  
                   
    

                 
           
                            
                     
                     Lloyd C. Blankfein, chairman and chief executive officer of Goldman Sachs Group Inc., testifies at a Senate Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs subcommittee hearing on Wall Street and the financial crisis, in Washington, D.C., on April 27, 2010. Photographer: Chris Kleponis  
                   
    

                 
           
                            
                     
                     Senator Carl Levin, a Democrat from Michigan, left, speaks with Senator John McCain, a Republican from Arizona, during a Senate Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs subcommittee hearing on Wall Street and the financial crisis in Washington, D.C., on April 27, 2010. Photographer: Joshua Roberts/Bloomberg  
                   
    

                 
           
                            
                     
                     Lloyd C. Blankfein, chairman and chief executive officer of Goldman Sachs Group Inc., leaves a hearing on Wall Street and the financial crisis in Washington, D.C., U.S., on April 27, 2010. Photographer: Joshua Roberts/Bloomberg  
                           

     
